5|first=Nicole|last=Bitette|title=Chris Rock, Malaak Compton finalize divorce after 20 years of marriage|work=NewYork Daily News|date=August 23, 2016|accessdate=November 13, 2016|archive-date=2018-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623113000/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/chris-rock-malaak-compton-divorce-20-years-article-1.2762085|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==爭議==
===第88屆奧斯卡種族歧視事件===
虽然主持人克里斯·洛克的主持表现获得多数人的好评，但他后来因和萨沙·拜伦·科恩在舞台上拿亚洲人的刻板形象和好战性格开玩笑而受到批评。节目期间，洛克带着三名扮成会计师的亚裔孩子走上舞台，表示“他们是最敬业、细心和勤奋的代表……有请明珠（{{lang|en|Ming Zhu}}）、保灵（{{lang|en|Bao Ling}}）和大卫·莫斯科维茨（{{lang|en|David Moskowitz}}）”。他继续说道，“如果有人被这个笑话困扰到了，只管用你那也是由这些孩子生产的手机发推文就可以了<ref name=wapost>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/29/the-oscars-were-all-about-diversity-but-people-hated-that-asian-joke/|title=If the Oscars were all about diversity, why the crude Asian joke?|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=2016-07-10|archive-date=2016-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323085844/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/29/the-oscars-were-all-about-diversity-but-people-hated-that-asian-joke/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

此外，以阿里G身份与[[奥利维亚·维尔德|奥利维亚·维尔德]]一同颁奖的拜伦·科恩表示：“那些拿着卑微的越南盾薪水、兢兢业业、细心且勤奋的小黄人怎能没有奥斯卡奖。你不知道，这才是小黄人。”Slate的刘罗文指出了这个针对亚洲人的双关语笑话<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2016/02/29/why_chris_rock_and_ali_g_s_racist_asian_jokes_at_the_oscars_were_such_a.html|title=Why Chris Rock's Asian Joke Was Such a Disappointment.|work=Slate.com|author=Liu, Lowen|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229181927/http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2016/02/29/why_chris_rock_and_ali_g_s_racist_asian_jokes_at_the_oscars_were_such_a.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。拜伦·科恩的妻子、演员艾拉·费雪在他登台前帮他穿上角色的服装。她表示活动制作人曾明确授权他以其饰演的任何角色亮相，但她表示碰到洛克后拜伦的想法大胆了起来，这让他對执行這计划有了信心<ref name="VultureCohen">{{cite web|last1=Lockett|first1=Dee|last2=Fitz-Gerald|first2=Sean|title=Sacha Baron Cohen Wasn’t Allowed to Do Ali G at the Oscars, So Isla Fisher Helped Him Slip Into the Costume Right Before Going On|url=http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/sacha-baron-cohens-ali-g-crashed-the-oscars.html|website=Vulture.com|publisher=Vulture|accessdate=2016-07-10|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320152401/http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/sacha-baron-cohens-ali-g-crashed-the-oscars.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

除了公众的批评，尤其是在網路上<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/child-labor-isn-t-funny-twitter-reacts-oscars-asian-joke-n527731|author=Lee, Traci G.|title=Oscars 2016: Twitter Reacts to 'Asian Joke' at Academy Awards|work=NBC News|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229100655/http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/child-labor-isn-t-funny-twitter-reacts-oscars-asian-joke-n527731|dead-url=no}}</ref>，笑话还被《[[GQ|GQ]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gq.com/story/chris-rock-asian-joke-oscars|title=Why Chris Rock's Awkward Oscars Joke About Asian People Fell Flat|author=Gayomali, Chris|work=GQ|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301104657/http://www.gq.com/story/chris-rock-asian-joke-oscars|dead-url=no}}</ref>、《[[好莱坞报道者|好莱坞报道者]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-why-make-cheap-jokes-871623|title=Oscars: Why Make Cheap Jokes at the Expense of Asians?|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301014858/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-why-make-cheap-jokes-871623|dead-url=no}}</ref>、《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/01/movies/chris-rocks-asian-joke-at-oscars-provokes-backlash.html?smid=fb-nytimes&smtyp=cur|title=Chris Rock's Asian Joke at Oscars Provokes Backlash|work=The New York Times|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303021849/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/01/movies/chris-rocks-asian-joke-at-oscars-provokes-backlash.html?smid=fb-nytimes&smtyp=cur|dead-url=no}}</ref>和《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》批评<ref name=wapost/>。《华盛顿邮报》的杰西卡·康特雷拉（{{lang|en|Jessica Contrera}}）指出：“缺乏多样性中再有缺乏多样性。最为明显的是洛克将三名亚裔儿童领到台上，称之为金融公司[[普华永道|普华永道]]的‘银行家’<ref name=wapost/>。”《[[初来乍到|初来乍到]]》演员[[吴恬敏|吴恬敏]]和篮球运动员[[林书豪|林书豪]]也谈到了笑话，前者表示“让小孩在舞台上游行，说着几乎是种族主义笑话的笑柄台词非常以简释繁，让人很不愉快。”后者在Twitter上称他“厌倦了被用‘酷’和‘好啦’砸亚洲人<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeremy-lin-slams-oscars-host-871641|title=Jeremy Lin Slams Chris Rock's Asian Jokes|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301062029/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeremy-lin-slams-oscars-host-871641|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

2016年3月9日，由台湾著名导演[[李安|李安]]、著名美籍日裔演员[[乔治·武井|乔治·武井]]、美籍华裔纪录片导演[[楊紫燁|楊紫燁]]等25位亚裔美国电影艺术与科学学院成员美籍华裔电影人以及美籍华裔电影人[[曾奕田|曾奕田]]、迪士尼动画导演{{le|唐·霍尔|Don Hall (filmmaker)}}等原美国电影艺术与科学学院成员联名向学院发出抗议信<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/ang-lee-george-takei-25-875772 |title=Ang Lee, George Takei Among 25 Academy Members Protesting Oscars' Asian Jokes |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2016-03-15 |accessdate=2016-03-16 |archive-date=2016-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624232721/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/ang-lee-george-takei-25-875772 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。最终学院发表公开声明正式致歉<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/03/16/470722236/academys-apology-for-asian-jokes-at-oscars-falls-flat |title=Academy's Apology For Asian Jokes At Oscars Falls Flat |work=NPR |date=2016-03-16 |accessdate=2016-03-19 |archive-date=2016-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319014648/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/03/16/470722236/academys-apology-for-asian-jokes-at-oscars-falls-flat |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===第94届奥斯卡掌摑事件===
2022年3月27日，在[[第94届奥斯卡金像奖|第94届奥斯卡金像奖]]颁发[[奥斯卡最佳纪录片奖|奥斯卡最佳纪录片]]的洛克在发言中嘲讽演員[[威尔·史密斯|威尔·史密斯]]的妻子[[贾达·萍克特·史密斯|贾达·萍克特·史密斯]]脱发的样子像在演《[[魔鬼女大兵|魔鬼女大兵]]》，起初威爾史密斯面對玩笑保持微笑，然而當他注意到妻子的不悅{{FACT}}，隨即走上台向其掌摑，事后叫他“嘴里少提我老婆的名字”<ref>{{cite web |title='CODA' wins best picture Oscar, marking a streaming first |url=https://apnews.com/article/2022-oscars-show-9a69424884de11649b68a12a284353a1 |website=AP NEWS |accessdate=2022-03-28 |date=2022-03-26 |archive-date=2022-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328005634/https://apnews.com/article/2022-oscars-show-9a69424884de11649b68a12a284353a1 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Desta |first1=Yohana |title=Will Smith Slaps Chris Rock at Oscars 2022 After Joke Gone Wrong |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2022/03/will-smith-chris-rock-oscars |access-date=2022-03-28 |work=Vanity Fair |date=2022-03-28 |archive-date=2022-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328033949/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2022/03/will-smith-chris-rock-oscars }}</ref>。有关画面被美国转播商[[美国广播公司|美国广播公司]]紧急消音，但被海外转播方（如澳大利亚的[[七號電視網|七號電視網]]和日本的[[WOWOW|WOWOW]]）原音呈现，并在网路上快速传播<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hibberd |first=James |last2=Hibberd |first2=James |date=2022-03-28 |title=Will Smith Slaps Chris Rock on Oscars Stage in Shock Moment After Jada Pinkett Smith Joke |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/will-smith-chris-rock-oscars-1235120096/ |access-date=2022-03-28 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328051813/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/will-smith-chris-rock-oscars-1235120096/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Author |first=No |date=2022-03-28 |title=In viral moment, best actor winner Will Smith smacks Chris Rock at Oscars |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2022/03/28/films/will-smith-slaps-chris-rock/ |access-date=2022-03-28 |website=The Japan Times |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328104046/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2022/03/28/films/will-smith-slaps-chris-rock/ }}</ref>。后来威尔·史密斯赢得[[奥斯卡最佳男主角|最佳男主角]]时解釋自己的行為，但未有向洛克道歉<ref>{{cite web |title=Will Smith appeared to hit Chris Rock at the Oscars over joke about Jada Pinkett Smith |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/will-smith-appears-hit-chris-rock-joke-wife-rcna21775 |website=NBC News |accessdate=2022-03-28 |date=2022-03-28 |archive-date=2022-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220329075609/https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/will-smith-appears-hit-chris-rock-joke-wife-rcna21775 }}</ref>。

其後史密斯已正式發出書面道歉聲明，包括向洛克致歉。

